SIMPLE: unclean
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unclean
<hw>Un*clean"</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*kl⟦emac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>uncl⟦aemac⟧ne</ets>. See <er>Unnot</er>, and <er>Clean</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Not clean; foul; dirty; filthy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Ceremonially impure; needing ritual
cleansing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that toucheth the dead body of any man shall be
<qex>unclean</qex> seven days.</q> <rj><qau>Num. xix. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Morally impure.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Adultery of the heart,
consisting of inordinate and <xex>unclean</xex> affections.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Perkins.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*clean"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*clean"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Unclean animals</b></col> <fld>(Script.)</fld>, <cd>those
which the Israelites were forbidden to use for food.</cd> --
<col><b>Unclean spirit</b></col> <fld>(Script.)</fld>, <cd>a wicked
spirit; a demon.</cd> <au>Mark i. 27.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncleansable</ent>⟦br⟧
